AWS S3 Static Website Hosting Project

Project Overview
This project demonstrates how to host a static website using Amazon S3

The goal was to build a simple, publicly accessible website stored in an S3 bucket, apply the correct permissions, bucket policies, and versioning ,
and implement a lifecycle configuration for cost optimization.

AWS Services Used
- Amazon S3 — for object storage and website hosting  
- AWS IAM — for managing permissions and access control  
- Amazon S3 Versioning — to maintain older file versions  
- Amazon S3 Lifecycle Rules — to automatically transition or delete old versions  
- AWS Management Console — for configuration and testing  
